Function to recode child anthropometric indicators and calculate anthropometric z-scores

Source: R/03-recode_anthro.R
recode_anthro.Rd

Function to recode child anthropometric indicators and calculate anthropometric z-scores

recode_anthro(
  df,
  core.columns = c("enumDate", "geo_rural", "geo_state", "geo_villward"),
  flag = TRUE,
  cases = TRUE
)

Arguments

df

A data.frame collected for the Myanmar MCCT Programme Evaluation Study containing anthropometric data
core.columns

A vector of variable names to include in resulting
flag

Logical. Should WHO flagging criteria be applied to the z-scores? Default is TRUE.
cases

Logical. Should cases of child undernutrition be assessed? Default is TRUE.

Value

A data.frame of recoded anthropometric measurements and z-scores

Examples

recode_anthro(df = create_canthro(df = childAnthro, x = anthroDF))
